Feature: User registration (example)
  As a new user
  I want to register an account
  So that I can access the protected API

  REQ-002: When a user submits valid registration JSON to POST /auth/register,
           the system shall return 201 with the stored user record.

  Scenario: Successful registration with valid JSON
    Given the system has no user with email "alice@example.net"
    When a POST is made to /auth/register with body:
      """
      {"email": "alice@example.net", "password_hash": "$argon2id$v=19$m=65536$..."}
      """
    Then the response status is 201
    And the response body contains the field "id"
    And the response body field "email" equals "alice@example.net"

  REQ-003: If the registration JSON fails schema validation,
           then the system shall return 422 with a per-field error list.

  Scenario: Registration fails on missing email
    When a POST is made to /auth/register with body:
      """
      {"password_hash": "$argon2id$..."}
      """
    Then the response status is 422
    And the response body field "errors[0].field" equals "email"
    And the response body field "errors[0].message" contains "required"
